gobblin.metastore

Class ZkStateStore<T extends State>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.metastore.ZkStateStore<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - state object type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    StateStore<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ZkDatasetStateStore

    public class ZkStateStore<T extends State>
extends Object
implements StateStore<T>
    An implementation of StateStore backed by ZooKeeper.

    This implementation stores serialized States as a blob in ZooKeeper in the Sequence file format. The ZK path is in the format /STORE_ROOT_DIR/STORE_NAME/TABLE_NAME. State keys are state IDs (see State.getId()), and values are objects of State or any of its extensions. Keys will be empty strings if state IDs are not set (i.e., State.getId() returns null). In this case, the get(String, String, String) method may not work.
